TY  - JOUR
T1  - Differential Effects of Incentive Motivators on Work Performance
AU  - Stajkovic, Alexander D.
AU  - Luthans, Fred
Y1  - 2001/06/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069372
DO  - 10.5465/3069372
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 580
EP  - 590
VL  - 44
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this field experiment, we first compared the performance effects of money systematically administered through the organizational behavior modification (O.B. Mod.) model and routine pay for performance and then compared the effects of O.B. Mod.-administered money, social recognition, and performance feedback. The money intervention based on the O.B. Mod. outperformed routine pay for performance (performance increase = 37% vs. 11%) and also had stronger effects on performance than social recognition (24%) and performance feedback (20%).
AB  - In this field experiment, we first compared the performance effects of money systematically administered through the organizational behavior modification (O.B. Mod.) model and routine pay for performance and then compared the effects of O.B. Mod.-administered money, social recognition, and performance feedback. The money intervention based on the O.B. Mod. outperformed routine pay for performance (performance increase = 37% vs. 11%) and also had stronger effects on performance than social recognition (24%) and performance feedback (20%).
